target_text: Fewer hours of sleep on an average school night [is] associated with increased odds of all selected unsafe behaviors//the strongest associations in relation to mood and self-harm//Teens who slept for less than six hours per night were three times more likely to report considering suicide, planning a suicide attempt or attempting suicide, compared with teens who slept eight hours or more. They were also four times more likely to have reported a suicide attempt that resulted in them needing treatment
